I"a<ul>
  <li>
    <p>In the grub menu select actual kernel and type “-e”
<img src="../images/reseting-root-password/pic-1.png" alt="IMAGE" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Go to the line with “<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">linux 16</code>” and change <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ro</code> to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">rw init=/sysroot/bin/sh</code>”.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>before:
<img src="../images/reseting-root-password/pic-2.png" alt="IMAGE" /></p>

<p>after: 
<img src="../images/reseting-root-password/pic-3.png" alt="IMAGE" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Press <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ctrl+X</code> for starting a single mode session</p>
  </li>
  <li>When single mode is started access to the system…:
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>chroot /sysroot
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>And using passwd command change the root’s password:
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>passwd root
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Finally, it is necessary to update SELinux information by createing an empty <strong>.autorelabel</strong> in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/</code>
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>touch /.autorelabel
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Exit from single mode session</p>
  </li>
  <li>Try to login using a new password</li>
</ul>
:ET